window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Jodi thought he got over on Sabrina, but he had another thing coming....<br> <br> Jodi views himself as the upper echelon of Black men. Smart, successful, educated, and incredibly wealthy. He's got cars, clothes, and women, but that's where his problems begin. While he's supposed to be faithful to his longtime girlfriend, Sabrina, he figures what she doesn't know won't hurt her.<br> <br> Sabrina put her trust in Jodi when he moved her and her three-year-old son, Na'Vey, into his house. Little did she know, Jodi had a lot of secrets, and he wasn't the man she signed up to be with.<br> <br> Jodi feels like he has the upper hand, and there's nothing Sabrina can do about his philandering ways.<br> <br> But what Jodi doesn't seem to realize is that he might be a player, but even the king on a chessboard knows the queen controls the moves.</p> <p><i>Daddy's Home</i> is a gripping and thrilling urban drama about a man who has it all, but realizes it a little too late....</p>"; 
